Fig. 4. Ventral view of P4 of 

Lonchophylla handleyi

: (A) USNM 588021, (B) AMNH 230215; 

L. chocoana

: (C) ROM 105798, (D) ICN 4395; 

L. robusta

: (E) ICN 13648; 

L. orienticollina

: (F) ICN 10114. Note the differences in size, degree of development, and bluntness across species and individuals. A and C each have a cusp, but it is blunt compared to that of E or F. B has a small cusp, while D has an indistinct protuberance in place of a cusp.
